# Search case-insensitively unless the pattern contains uppercase letters.
--smart-case

# Search hidden files/dirs (e.g. .eslintrc, dotfiles). This does NOT
# disable .gitignore — ripgrep still honors the global core.excludesFile
# and every per-directory .gitignore.
--hidden

# Never descend into .git/ (ripgrep skips it already; explicit for clarity).
--glob=!.git/

# .gitignore (global + per-directory), .ignore, and .rgignore are honored
# by DEFAULT. Sensitive files such as .env stay excluded so secrets are not
# dumped to the terminal on every search. To bypass ignore rules for a
# single, deliberate search, pass a flag on that one invocation:
#   rg --no-ignore PATTERN .env   # search a specific ignored file
#   rg -u PATTERN                 # --no-ignore + search hidden
#   rg -uu PATTERN                # also search binary files
# A named helper `rg-secrets` is defined in the zsh config for this purpose.
